---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import IsotraceFigure from "../../components/IsotraceFigure.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Isotrace · Xiaochuan Li"
  description="Fictional concept names with path-encoded naming locate where compositional reasoning gives way to surface patterns — hop by hop, without opening the model."
>
  <article class="prose">
    <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-text-dim)] font-medium mb-2">
      Paper · in progress
    </div>
    <h1>Isotrace — behavioral tracing of multi-hop reasoning</h1>
    <p class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)] italic !text-lg !mb-8">
      Locating where shortcut substitution replaces compositional reasoning — without opening the model.
    </p>

    <p>
      <em>Detail page coming. The short version:</em> we use fictional concept names
      (<code>Zorb</code>, <code>Veln</code>, <code>Quasp</code>) whose naming conventions encode the
      multi-hop reasoning path. By comparing model outputs across an adversarial contrast — same
      surface names, different underlying facts — we can localize the hop at which the model stops
      reasoning compositionally and starts riding the naming pattern.
    </p>

    <IsotraceFigure />

    <p>
      The complementarity to <a href="/research/sc-certification">SC certification</a> is the point:
      that work asks <em>whether</em> a model's stable-correct behavior is grounded; Isotrace asks
      <em>where</em> the shortcut fires, hop by hop. Behavioral tracing and mechanistic
      interpretability as mutual validation.
    </p>

    <hr/>
    <p class="!text-sm !text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">An interactive demo will live here once the writeup is further along.</p>
  </article>
</Base>
